 {"id":"franken_networkx-kcompflow","title":"REVIEW: [LOW] k_components / edge_disjoint_paths / node_disjoint_paths missing parity kwargs","description":"k_components missing 'flow_func'; edge_disjoint_paths and node_disjoint_paths missing 'auxiliary' and 'residual'. Added at public surface for drop-in kwarg parity.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","close_reason":"Added missing parity kwargs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-ghtree","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] gomory_hu_tree stringified nodes + dropped cut-value weight attrs","description":"The Rust fast-path _fnx.gomory_hu_tree_rust returned a tree whose node identifiers were stringified ('0','1' instead of int 0,1) and whose edges lacked the cut-value 'weight' attribute that nx's tree carries. Drop-in callers that read 'tree.edges[u,v][\"weight\"]' got KeyError; pattern-matching on node type broke. Delegated the whole function to nx for correctness.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","close_reason":"Delegated to nx for correct node types and weight attrs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-swmsg","title":"REVIEW: [LOW] stoer_wagner error messages didn't match nx's 3 distinct wordings","description":"nx raises 3 different messages: 'graph has less than two nodes.', 'graph is not connected.', and (implicitly) the compute path when valid. fnx raised one generic 'stoer_wagner requires a connected graph with >= 2 nodes' for all preconditions. Pre-validated in the Python wrapper so regex pytest.raises(..., match='graph has less than two nodes') against upstream keeps working.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:02:03.000000000Z","close_reason":"Pre-validate in Python wrapper; raise nx-exact messages per case","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-isokw","title":"REVIEW: [LOW] iso/predicate/spanner first-param name mismatch (g vs G) + deg_sequence mismatch","description":"Several fnx functions re-exported directly from the Rust binding used lowercase 'g' as the first param, while nx uses 'G'. Kwarg-style drop-in calls like 'fnx.is_strongly_connected(G=digraph)' TypeError'd. Affected: fast_could_be_isomorphic, faster_could_be_isomorphic, is_strongly_connected, spanner. Similarly, is_valid_degree_sequence_havel_hakimi and is_valid_degree_sequence_erdos_gallai named the param 'sequence' where nx uses 'deg_sequence'. Added thin Python wrappers with the correct nx parameter names.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","close_reason":"Python wrappers with nx-matching param names","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-egoedgeord","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] ego_graph re-orients edges with ego node first (diverges from nx)","description":"fnx.ego_graph(G, n, radius=1) on fnx.path_graph(5) produced edges [(2, 1), (2, 3)] while nx produced [(1, 2), (2, 3)]. The Rust fast-path '_fnx.ego_graph_rust' re-orients every edge with the ego node as the first endpoint, losing the input graph's edge orientation. Reworked the Python wrapper to always compute the node set in Python (BFS/dijkstra) and copy edges from G in original insertion order — no more Rust fast-path for this function.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","close_reason":"Always use Python path; preserve G's edge orientation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-assortkw","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] degree_assortativity_coefficient missing x/y/weight/nodes kwargs","description":"nx.degree_assortativity_coefficient(G, x='out', y='in', weight=None, nodes=None) — fnx's Rust binding exposed only (g). Users passing weight= or x=/y= variants TypeError'd. Added a Python wrapper that delegates to nx for any non-default kwarg while keeping the Rust fast-path for the plain default call. Verified weighted / in-out / nodes-filter all match nx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","close_reason":"Python wrapper delegates to nx for non-default kwargs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-effkw","title":"REVIEW: [LOW] efficiency / global_efficiency / local_efficiency used 'g' instead of 'G'","description":"Kwarg-style drop-in calls fnx.global_efficiency(G=graph) TypeError'd because the Rust binding named the param 'g'. Wrapped in thin Python shims with G as first param.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","close_reason":"Python wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-copyedgeord","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] Graph(fnx_src) / G.copy() / G.to_undirected() reverse edge orientation","description":"fnx.Graph(src).copy() on src = Graph with edges [(0,1),(1,2)] yields [(0,1),(2,1)] — the second edge reversed. Similarly G.copy(as_view=False) and G.to_undirected(as_view=False) emit edges in canonical-smallest-endpoint-first sometimes and reversed other times, diverging from nx which preserves original insertion order. Pre-existing Rust-side bug surfaced after rebuild. Needs a Rust-side fix in the constructor/copy paths. Queued.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
